Key Match Events: Bradley Beal scored 25 points off the bench, leading the Suns to a 123-115 victory over the Hawks.
Kevin Durant added 23 points for the Suns.
Devin Booker contributed 20 points and 12 assists despite shooting 0 of 8 from 3-point range.
Grayson Allen scored 23 points and hit his fifth 3-pointer to give the Suns a 120-105 lead with 3:26 left.
Trae Young led the Hawks with 21 points and seven assists.
Durant, Tyus Jones, and Allen hit three straight 3s to give the Suns a 120-105 lead with 4:03 left.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Suns shot 57.6% from the field.
The Hawks missed forward Jalen Johnson, who missed a third straight game with right shoulder inflammation.
